So trying to control my KAKU from HAOS. The first step is to get a cc1101 working on an ESP32 (a S3 in my case).

I use these two libraries:
*  https://github.com/1technophile/NewRemoteSwitch
*  https://github.com/LSatan/SmartRC-CC1101-Driver-Lib

My cc1101 has following Pinout:
cc1101        ESP32-S3
GND        -> GND
3.3v       -> 3v3
GDO0       -> 39
CSN        -> 40
SCK        -> 9
MOSI       -> 42
GDO1/GOD1  -> 12
GDO2       -> 13

I used the Learncode_cc1101 example and modified it:
- set my SPI pins (cc1101.setSpiPin())
- set the GDO pins (cc1101.setGDO())
- changed the interrupt pin to GDO2 for newRemoteReceiver (GDO0 is used for transmit)
